We call the vertex $u$ a \emph{reservoir vertex} and the absorber $A$ a \emph{$u$-absorber} . The \emph{inner vertices} of $A$ are the vertices from $V^*(C)\cup\bigcup_i V^*(P_i)$. The vertices $v_1$ and $v_{t+1}$ are referred to as the \emph{main endpoints} of $A$.

