\label{def:linearIsomorphic}
Two systems of linear forms $\mathcal{L}_0 $ and $\mathcal{L}_1$ are \emph{isomorphic} if and only if there exists
a \emph{bijection} from $\mathcal{L}_0$ to $\mathcal{L}_1$  that can be extended to an \emph{invertible} linear transformation $T: {\rm span}(\mathcal{L}_0) \rightarrow {\rm span}(\mathcal{L}_1)$.

