Let $k \in \mathbb{N}_0$, and let $D$ be a digraph. We say that $D$ has \emph{directed modular width at most} $k$, if one of the following holds:
	\begin{itemize}
		\item $|V(D)| \leq k$, or
		\item There exists a partition of $V(D)$ into $\ell \in \{2,\ldots,k\}$ modules $M_1, \ldots, M_\ell$ such that for every $i$, $D[M_i]$ has directed modular width at most $k$.
	\end{itemize}
	The least $k \ge 1$ for which a digraph $D$ has directed modular width at most $k$ is now defined to be the \emph{directed modular width} , denoted by $\dmw(D)$, of $D$.

